                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16841008-15-off67 t16841008-15-cd70"></join> past, the said Esq; Coghill and most part of his Family being at Church, two Maid-Servants and an old Gentlewoman only left at Home, four Men came and knocked at the Door, which being opened by one of the Maids, they rushed in, shut to the Door, and Robb'd the House of the Goods before-mentioned, abuseing the old Gentlewoman, and Breaking her Arm. It was also in Evidence, that Shaw had Imployed one Carr to go and Sell the Tankard; which Carr being questioned where he had it, produced Shaw, and Shaw owned it to be his Tankard; but upon further enquiry, it was found to be one of the Tankards Stolen from Mr. Coghill. Upon the whole, Shaw was found <rs id="t16841008-15-verdict71" type="verdictDescription">
